{"word":"G5495 - χείρ - cheír - khire - Hand","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>மூல வார்த்தை / Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">χείρ</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>எழுத்துமாற்றம் / Transliteration: </strong>cheír"},{"paragraph":"<strong>ஒலிபெயர்ப்பு / Phonetic: </strong>khire"},{"paragraph":"<strong>சுருக்க விளக்கம் / Short Definition: </strong>Hand"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"கை, கரம் - பெண்பால் பெயர்ச்சொல்"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"the hand"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"parts-of-speech\"><strong>Part(s) of speech:</strong> Noun Feminine / பெயர்ச்சொல் (பெண்பால்)</span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"original-in-english\"><strong>ஆங்கில மூலம் / Original in English:</strong> Perhaps from the base of <a href=\"#/G5494 - χειμών - cheimṓn - khi-mone'/5494\">G5494</a> in the sense of its congener the base of <a href=\"#/G5490 - χάσμα - chásma - khas'-mah/5490\">G5490</a> (through the idea of <i>hollowness</i> for grasping); the <i>hand</i> (literally or figuratively [<i>power</i>]; especially [by Hebraism] a <i>means</i> or <i>instrument</i>): - hand."},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G5495 - χείρ - cheír - khire/5495\">G5495</a>, <a href=\"#/G5496 - χειραγωγέω - cheiragōgéō - khi-rag-ogue-eh'-o/5496\">G5496</a>, <a href=\"#/G5497 - χειραγωγός - cheiragōgós - khi-rag-o-gos'/5497\">G5497</a>, <a href=\"#/G5498 - χειρόγραφον - cheirógraphon - khi-rog'-raf-on/5498\">G5498</a>, <a href=\"#/G5499 - χειροποίητος - cheiropoíētos - khi-rop-oy'-ay-tos/5499\">G5499</a>, <a href=\"#/G5500 - χειροτονέω - cheirotonéō - khi-rot-on-eh'-o/5500\">G5500</a>, <a href=\"#/G886 - ἀχειροποίητος - acheiropoíētos - akh-i-rop-oy'-ay-tos/886\">G886</a>"}]}